				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "About explaining the interface, I ask people to describe out loud what they see. The first time they do it, they only see the contents. But then I ask them to alt+click on the view to get the source and then to go to the Meta. And then I ask them if they can understand what’s in front of them. They usually do not (even seasoned developers at Lifeware). Then I ask them to read the interface from top to bottom.\nThe metaphor I use here: say you end up on a website that tries to fish your credentials; it looks exactly like the one you are used to, but the meaning is completely different. In that situation, if you only look at the contents, you cannot make the right decision. That is why you read any website starting from the url at the top.\nIn typical environments, positions on a screen are typically linked to specific meaning (e.g., edtior is in the center, the right pane is the index with folders and files). In GT, the meaning of the tool can change at any time. That is why before interpreting the output of the tool, you first have to understand the meaning of the tool and that starts with reading the interface from top to bottom."
